org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.util.consensus

Class ConicConsensusCaller

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.util.consensus.ConicConsensusCaller
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConsensusCaller

    public class ConicConsensusCaller
extends Object
    ConicConsensusCaller calls consensus using the "Conic Ambiguity Model". The model is called the Conic Model because it uses a multidimensional cone to define the region of ambiguity. Cumulative quality values for each base call are represented by vectors, if the resulting vector falls within the region of ambiguity, then the consensus is ambiguous. Geometric symmetry allows the math to be simplified to only 2 dimensions.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Field Detail

      • DEFAULT_CONIC_AMBIGUITY_ANGLE

        public static final double DEFAULT_CONIC_AMBIGUITY_ANGLE
        The angle 36.8698977 degrees was the angle that was found to most often match expert human consensus callers in TIGR experiments performed in 2003 on Sanger data.

        TIGR data to validate the conic model and was used to come up with this angle is available http://slicetools.sourceforge.net/libSlice/worksheet.xls and http://slicetools.sourceforge.net/libSlice/results.xls
